# Set Up Request Validation

## Arguments
- `service`: Service name
- `routes`: Comma-separated route paths to validate (e.g., `POST /users,PUT /users/:id`)

## Architecture

```
Request â†’ validate({ body, query, params }) â†’ Zod parse â†’ handler
                                            â†“ fail
                                    422 ValidationError
```

## Steps

### 1. Add Dependencies
- Add `@ironplate/validation` to `apps/{service}/package.json`
- Run `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} install`

### 2. Define Schemas

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';
import { uuid, email, nonEmptyString, pagination } from '@ironplate/validation';

export const createUserSchema = z.object({
  name: nonEmptyString,
  email: email,
  role: z.enum(['admin', 'member', 'viewer']).default('member'),
});

export const getUsersQuerySchema = pagination.extend({
  role: z.enum(['admin', 'member', 'viewer']).optional(),
  search: z.string().optional(),
});

export const userIdParams = z.object({
  id: uuid,
});

export type CreateUserDto = z.infer<typeof createUserSchema>;
```

### 3. Apply Validation Middleware

```typescript
import { validate } from '@ironplate/validation';
import { Router } from 'express';

const router = Router();

router.post(
  '/users',
  validate({ body: createUserSchema }),
  async (req, res) => {
    // req.body is typed and validated
    const user = await createUser(req.body);
    res.status(201).json(user);
  },
);

router.get(
  '/users',
  validate({ query: getUsersQuerySchema }),
  async (req, res) => {
    // req.query.page, req.query.limit are numbers
    const users = await listUsers(req.query);
    res.json(users);
  },
);

router.get(
  '/users/:id',
  validate({ params: userIdParams }),
  async (req, res) => {
    // req.params.id is a valid UUID
    const user = await getUser(req.params.id);
    res.json(user);
  },
);
```

### 4. Combine Body + Query + Params

```typescript
router.put(
  '/users/:id',
  validate({
    params: userIdParams,
    body: createUserSchema.partial(), // all fields optional for updates
  }),
  updateUser,
);
```

## Built-in Schemas

| Schema | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `uuid` | string | UUID v4 format |
| `email` | string | Valid email, lowercased |
| `nonEmptyString` | string | Trimmed, min length 1 |
| `url` | string | Valid URL |
| `isoDate` | string | ISO 8601 datetime |
| `positiveInt` | number | Integer > 0 |
| `nonNegativeInt` | number | Integer >= 0 |
| `pagination` | object | `{ page, limit }` with defaults |
| `sort` | object | `{ sortBy, sortOrder }` |
| `slug` | string | Kebab-case URL-safe |
| `commaSeparatedList` | stringâ†’array | Splits on comma |
| `semver` | string | Semantic version |

## CRITICAL Rules
- ALWAYS validate at the route level â€” never trust client input
- ALWAYS use `validate()` middleware â€” never call `schema.parse()` manually in routes
- Use `.partial()` for update endpoints (PATCH/PUT with optional fields)
- The middleware strips unknown keys by default (safe against mass assignment)
- Validation errors return 422 with structured error details
- Use `z.coerce.number()` for query params (they arrive as strings)

## Checklist
- [ ] `@ironplate/validation` dependency added
- [ ] Zod schemas defined for all route inputs
- [ ] `validate()` middleware applied to all routes accepting input
- [ ] Query params use coercion (`z.coerce.number()`)
- [ ] Update routes use `.partial()` schemas
- [ ] Schema types exported for handler typing (`z.infer<typeof schema>`)
